`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
For testing Tone.js (which needs AudioContext), follow the "Three.js mock cast pattern": `jest.mock("tone", ...)` at module level replaces all Tone imports. Since Tone nodes are only constructed inside `initialize()` (not at module load), the mock works without special hoisting tricks. Access mock internals via `(Volume as unknown as jest.Mock).mock.results[0].value` — the `.results` array holds actual return values, which is crucial when a constructor `return`s a specific object (as mock implementations often do).
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
